'''Shyster''' may refer to:

* ([[description]]) A '''shyster''' is someone who acts in a disreputable, unethical or unscrupulous way, especially in the practice of law and politics, or a [[con artist]]. The word probably originated from the carnival game "Coconut Shy," given the reputation carnival workers and their games have. Other possible origins include a real 19th-century New York lawyer named Scheuster, or possibly from German ''Scheisser'' - "incompetent worthless person," literally "defecator". This term has been used in [[Isaac Asimov]]'s short science-fiction robot story "Evidence". An atmosphere is created around a falsity and then proven wrong.
* ([[military]]) '''SS-3 Shyster''' is the [[NATO reporting name]] for the [[R-5]] [[theatre ballistic missile]].

